{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Neh|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"When Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the rest of our enemies heard that I had rebuilt the wall and that no gap was left in it —though at that time I had not installed the doors in the city gates —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"Sanballat and Geshem sent me a message: “Come, let’s meet together in the villages of the Ono Valley.” They were planning to harm me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"So I sent messengers to them, saying, “I am doing important work and cannot come down. Why should the work cease while I leave it and go down to you?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"Four times they sent me the same proposal, and I gave them the same reply.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"Sanballat sent me this same message a fifth time by his aide, who had an open letter in his hand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"In it was written:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"and have even set up the prophets in Jerusalem to proclaim on your behalf, “There is a king in Judah.” These rumors will be heard by the king. So come, let’s confer together.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"Then I replied to him, “There is nothing to these rumors you are spreading; you are inventing them in your own mind.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"For they were all trying to intimidate us, saying, “They will drop their hands from the work, and it will never be finished.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"I went to the house of Shemaiah son of Delaiah, son of Mehetabel, who was restricted to his house. He said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"But I said, “Should a man like me run away? How can someone like me enter the temple and live? I will not go.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"I realized that God had not sent him, because of the prophecy he spoke against me. Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"He was hired, so that I would be intimidated, do as he suggested, sin, and get a bad reputation, in order that they could discredit me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":14,"text":"My God, remember Tobiah and Sanballat for what they have done, and also the prophetess Noadiah and the other prophets who wanted to intimidate me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":15,"text":"The wall was completed in fifty-two days, on the twenty-fifth day of the month Elul.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":16,"text":"When all our enemies heard this, all the surrounding nations were intimidated and lost their confidence, for they realized that this task had been accomplished by our God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":17,"text":"During those days, the nobles of Judah sent many letters to Tobiah, and Tobiah’s letters came to them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":18,"text":"For many in Judah were bound by oath to him, since he was a son-in-law of Shecaniah son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter of Meshullam son of Berechiah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","bookOrder":15,"chapter":6,"verse":19,"text":"These nobles kept mentioning Tobiah’s good deeds to me, and they reported my words to him. And Tobiah sent letters to intimidate me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Neh","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,5,7,8,10,11,14,15,17],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Attempts to Discourage the Builders"},{"beforeVerse":10,"text":"Attempts to Intimidate Nehemiah"},{"beforeVerse":15,"text":"The Wall Completed"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the rest of our enemies "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:19","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" heard that I had rebuilt the wall and that no gap was left in it "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 4:6–7","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" —though at that time I had not installed the doors in the city gates "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 3:1","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" — "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Neh 2:19","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":19},{"label":"Neh 4:6–7","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":6},{"label":"Neh 3:1","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Sanballat and Geshem "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" sent me a message: “Come, let’s meet together in the villages of "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or together at Kephirim in"},{"kind":"text","text":" the Ono Valley.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 8:12","book":"1Ch","chapter":8,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" They were planning to harm me."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"1Ch 8:12","book":"1Ch","chapter":8,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or together at Kephirim in"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So I sent messengers to them, saying, “I am doing important work and cannot come down. Why should the work cease while I leave it and go down to you?” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Four times they sent me the same proposal, and I gave them the same reply."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Sanballat "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" sent me this same message a fifth time by his aide, who had an open letter in his hand. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In it was written:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and have even set up the prophets in Jerusalem to proclaim on your behalf, “There is a king in Judah.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zch 9:9","book":"Zec","chapter":9,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" These rumors will be heard by the king. So come, let’s confer together."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Zch 9:9","book":"Zec","chapter":9,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then I replied to him, “There is nothing to these rumors you are spreading; you are inventing them in your own mind.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jb 13:4","book":"Job","chapter":13,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 52:2","book":"Psa","chapter":52,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jb 13:4","book":"Job","chapter":13,"verse":4},{"label":"Ps 52:2","book":"Psa","chapter":52,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For they were all trying to intimidate "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" us, saying, “They will drop their hands from "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or will give up on"},{"kind":"text","text":" the work, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 4:4","book":"Ezr","chapter":4,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and it will never be finished.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3},{"label":"Ezr 4:4","book":"Ezr","chapter":4,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or will give up on"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I went to the house of Shemaiah son of Delaiah, son of Mehetabel, who was restricted to his house. He said:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But I said, “Should a man like me run away? How can someone like me enter the temple and live? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 18:7","book":"Num","chapter":18,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" I will not go.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 18:7","book":"Num","chapter":18,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I realized that God had not sent him, because of the prophecy he spoke against me. Tobiah and Sanballat "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" had hired him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He was hired, so that I would be intimidated, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" do as he suggested, sin, and get a bad reputation, in order that they could discredit me."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"My God, remember "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 13:29","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":29,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Tobiah and Sanballat for what they have done, and also the prophetess Noadiah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 2:20","book":"Rev","chapter":2,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the other prophets who wanted to intimidate me."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 13:29","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":29},{"label":"Rv 2:20","book":"Rev","chapter":2,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The wall was completed "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 4:1","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 4:7","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" in fifty-two days, on the twenty-fifth day of the month Elul. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 6:15","book":"Ezr","chapter":6,"verse":15,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 4:1","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":1},{"label":"Neh 4:7","book":"Neh","chapter":4,"verse":7},{"label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1},{"label":"Ezr 6:15","book":"Ezr","chapter":6,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When all our enemies "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" heard this, all the surrounding nations were intimidated "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and lost their confidence, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit and fell greatly in their eyes"},{"kind":"text","text":" for they realized that this task had been accomplished by our God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 14:25","book":"Exo","chapter":14,"verse":25,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 2:10","book":"Neh","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1},{"label":"Ezr 3:3","book":"Ezr","chapter":3,"verse":3},{"label":"Ex 14:25","book":"Exo","chapter":14,"verse":25}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit and fell greatly in their eyes"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"During those days, the nobles of Judah sent many letters to Tobiah, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 13:4–5","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 13:7","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Tobiah’s letters came to them. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 6:1","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":1},{"label":"Neh 13:4–5","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":4},{"label":"Neh 13:7","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For many in Judah were bound by oath "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 10:5","book":"Ezr","chapter":10,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to him, since he was a son-in-law of Shecaniah son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter of Meshullam "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 3:4","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 3:30","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":30,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Berechiah. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezr 10:5","book":"Ezr","chapter":10,"verse":5},{"label":"Neh 3:4","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":4},{"label":"Neh 3:30","book":"Neh","chapter":3,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Neh:6:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"These nobles kept mentioning Tobiah’s good deeds to me, and they reported my words to him. And Tobiah sent letters to intimidate "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:9","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:13","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" me."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 6:9","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":9},{"label":"Neh 6:13","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099342061}